CREATE TABLE `isb-cgc.TCGA_bioclin_v0.clinical_v1`
(
  case_gdc_id STRING OPTIONS(description="GDC unique identifer for this case; e.g. 7b4ce492-ff40-4bf1-b3e8-75ff83e8746d. This identifier can be used to find more information at the GDC Data Portal ( https://portal.gdc.cancer.gov/cases/7b4ce492-ff40-4bf1-b3e8-75ff83e8746d )"),
  case_barcode STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA patient/case barcode; e.g. TCGA-06-0119"),
  program_name STRING OPTIONS(description="Program Name, always TCGA (The Cancer Genome Atlas) in this table."),
  disease_code STRING OPTIONS(description="A code representing the type of cancer. Values can be found at https://gdc.cancer.gov/resources-TCGA-users/TCGA-code-tables/TCGA-study-abbreviations; e.g. OV, GBM, LUAD"),
  project_short_name STRING OPTIONS(description="Project name abbreviation; the program name appended with a project name abbreviation; e.g. TCGA-OV, etc."),
  age_at_diagnosis INT64 OPTIONS(description="Age, in years, at which a condition or disease was first diagnosed"),
  age_began_smoking_in_years STRING OPTIONS(description="Age, in years, that the participant began smoking"),
  anatomic_neoplasm_subdivision STRING OPTIONS(description="The spatial location, subdivisions and/or atomic site name of a tumor; e.g. Rectum, Larynx, Tonsil, etc."),
  batch_number INT64 OPTIONS(description="The BCR Batch Code; see https://gdc.cancer.gov/resources-TCGA-users/TCGA-code-tables/bcr-batch-codes for explanation of the codes"),
  bcr STRING OPTIONS(description="Biospecimen Core Resource; e.g. Nationwide Children's Hospital, Washington University"),
  bmi FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="Body Mass Index of participant"),
  clinical_M STRING OPTIONS(description="The clinical M score is a rating of metastasis, that is, how much cancer has spread to distant sites. It is based on results of tests done before surgery, such as physical exams and imaging scans; e.g. MX, M0, M1"),
  clinical_N STRING OPTIONS(description="The clinical N score is a rating of the extent of cancer within nearby lymph nodes, based on results of tests done before surgery, such as physical exams and imaging scans; e.g. N1, N2, N3"),
  clinical_stage STRING OPTIONS(description="The stage of the cancer, based on results of tests done before surgery, such as physical exams and imaging scans; e.g. Stage I, Stage II, Stage III, Stage IV"),
  clinical_T STRING OPTIONS(description="The clinical T score is a rating of the extent of the primary tumor, based on results of tests done before surgery, such as physical exams and imaging scans; e.g. T1, T2, T3, T4"),
  colorectal_cancer STRING OPTIONS(description="Indicates whether the participant has colorectal cancer; e.g. Yes, No"),
  country STRING OPTIONS(description="Country of the participant; e.g. Germany, United States, Canada, etc."),
  days_to_birth INT64 OPTIONS(description="Days since birth (a negative value, relative to the date of diagnosis which is considered to be t=0)"),
  days_to_death INT64 OPTIONS(description="If vital_status indicates 'dead', then this is the number of days to death (a positive value) relative to the date of diagnosis."),
  days_to_initial_pathologic_diagnosis INT64 OPTIONS(description="The number of days to initial pathologic diagnosis"),
  days_to_last_followup INT64 OPTIONS(description="If vital_status indicates 'alive', then this is the number of days from the date of diagnosis to the last followup (communication contact)."),
  days_to_last_known_alive INT64 OPTIONS(description="Number of days from the date of diagnosis to the last day on which a person was known to be alive. This field is a combination of the days_to_last_followup and days_to death fields. Therefore, this field can be used whether the vital_status is 'alive' or 'dead'."),
  days_to_submitted_specimen_dx STRING OPTIONS(description="Numeric value to represent the day of the diagnosis for the submitted sample."),
  ethnicity STRING OPTIONS(description="The ethnic origination of a participant, independent from race; eg. Not Hispanic or Latino, Hispanic or Latino"),
  gender STRING OPTIONS(description="Participant gender; e.g. Male, Female"),
  gleason_score_combined STRING OPTIONS(description="The Gleason Score (ranging from 1 -5) is the grade of the aggressiveness of prostate cancer. The combined Gleason Score is the primary Gleason score  (for the largest area of the tumor) added to the secondary Gleason Score (for the next largest section of the tumor)."),
  h_pylori_infection STRING OPTIONS(description="Indicator of previous or current diagnosis of Helicobactor pylori infection; e.g. Yes, No, Never, Current"),
  height INT64 OPTIONS(description="Height of participant in centimeters"),
  histological_type STRING OPTIONS(description="The histological type of cancer; e.g. Adenosquamous, Astrocytoma, etc."),
  history_of_colon_polyps STRING OPTIONS(description="Indicator if the participant had a previous history of colon polyps as noted in the history/physical or previous endoscopic report(s); e.g. Yes, No"),
  history_of_neoadjuvant_treatment STRING OPTIONS(description="Describes the patient's history of neoadjuvant treatment and the kind of treament given prior to resection of the tumor; e.g. Yes, Pharmaceutical Treatment Prior to Resection, etc."),
  hpv_calls STRING OPTIONS(description="HPV strains; e.g. HPV18, HPV45, etc."),
  hpv_status STRING OPTIONS(description="Indicates whether the participant has a record of a positive finding for human papillomavirus; e.g. Positive, Negative, Indeterminate"),
  icd_10 STRING OPTIONS(description="Alphanumeric value used to describe the disease code from the tenth version of the International Classification of Disease (ICD-10)"),
  icd_o_3_histology STRING OPTIONS(description="Code that represents the histology of the disease using the third edition of the International Classification of Diseases for Oncology, published in 2000, used principally in tumor and cancer registries for coding the site (topography) and the histology (morphology) of neoplasms"),
  icd_o_3_site STRING OPTIONS(description="Code that represents the site of the disease using the third edition of the International Classification of Diseases for Oncology, published in 2000, used principally in tumor and cancer registries for coding the site (topography) and the histology (morphology) of neoplasms"),
  lymphatic_invasion STRING OPTIONS(description="Indicator if small or thin-walled vessel invasion is present, indicating lymphatic involvement; e.g. Yes, No"),
  lymphnodes_examined STRING OPTIONS(description="Indicator whether the lymph nodes were examined; e.g. Yes, No"),
  lymphovascular_invasion_present STRING OPTIONS(description="Indicator if  invasion of a cancer to the blood vessels and/or lymphatics invasion is present; e.g. Yes, No"),
  menopause_status STRING OPTIONS(description="A female participant's menopausal status; e.g. Post, Pre, Indeterminate, Peri"),
  mononucleotide_and_dinucleotide_marker_panel_analysis_status STRING OPTIONS(description="Status of the mononucleotide and dinucleotide marker panel analysis; microsatellite-stable (MSS), low level MSI (MSI-L) if less than 40% of markers were altered and high level MSI (MSI-H) if greater than 40% of markers were altered"),
  neoplasm_histologic_grade STRING OPTIONS(description="Rating which expresses the degree of abnormality of cancer cells, a measure of differentiation and aggressiveness; e.g. G1, G2, G3, G4"),
  new_tumor_event_after_initial_treatment BOOL OPTIONS(description="Indicates whether a patient has had a new tumor event after initial treatment; Yes, No"),
  number_of_lymphnodes_examined INT64 OPTIONS(description="The number of lymph nodes examined "),
  number_of_lymphnodes_positive_by_he STRING OPTIONS(description="The number of lymph nodes involved with disease as determined by histological examination"),
  number_pack_years_smoked INT64 OPTIONS(description="The number of packs smoked per day times the number of years smoked by the participant"),
  other_dx STRING OPTIONS(description="Indicator and type of other diagnosis; e.g. No; Yes, History of Prior Malignancy; Yes, History of Synchronous/Bilateral Malignancy; Both History of Synchronous/Bilateral and Prior Malignancy"),
  other_malignancy_anatomic_site STRING OPTIONS(description="The site on the body where the other malignancy occurred; e.g. Bladder, Uterus, etc."),
  other_malignancy_histological_type STRING OPTIONS(description="The histological type of cancer of the other malignancy; e.g. Adenosquamous, Astrocytoma, etc."),
  other_malignancy_type STRING OPTIONS(description="Indicates whether another malignancy occurred before or at the same time; e.g. Prior Malignancy, Synchronous Malignancy"),
  pathologic_M STRING OPTIONS(description="The pathologic M score is a rating of metastasis, that is, how much cancer has spread to distant sites. It is based on surgery or biopsy; e.g. MX, M0, M1"),
  pathologic_N STRING OPTIONS(description="The pathologic N score is a rating of the extent of cancer within nearby lymph nodes, based on surgery or biopsy; e.g. N1, N2, N3"),
  pathologic_stage STRING OPTIONS(description="The stage of the cancer, based on surgery or biopsy; e.g. Stage I, Stage II, Stage III, Stage IV"),
  pathologic_T STRING OPTIONS(description="The pathologic T score is a rating of the extent of the primary tumor, based on surgery or biopsy; e.g. T1, T2, T3, T4"),
  person_neoplasm_cancer_status STRING OPTIONS(description="The participant's cancer status; e.g. With Tumor, Tumor Free"),
  pregnancies STRING OPTIONS(description="The number of times (including currently if it applies) that a female participant has been pregnant, regardless of outcome."),
  primary_neoplasm_melanoma_dx STRING OPTIONS(description="Indicates whether a person had a primary diagnosis of melanoma; e.g. Yes, No"),
  primary_therapy_outcome_success STRING OPTIONS(description="Kind of outcome achieved after the completion of the initial course of treatment; e.g. Complete Remission/Response, Progressive Disease, etc."),
  psa_value STRING OPTIONS(description="A male participant's Prostrate-Specific Antigen (PSA) value"),
  race STRING OPTIONS(description="The race of a participant, independent from ethnicity; e.g. White, Black or African American, Asian, Native Hawaiian or other Pacific Islander, American Indian or Alaska Native"),
  residual_tumor STRING OPTIONS(description="Status of the tissue margin following surgical resection; e.g. R0, R1, R2, RX"),
  stopped_smoking_year INT64 OPTIONS(description="Four-digit year that the participant stopped smoking; e.g. 2010"),
  tobacco_smoking_history INT64 OPTIONS(description="Category describing current smoking status and smoking history as self-reported by a participant.; e.g. 1, 2, etc."),
  tss_code STRING OPTIONS(description="Tissue Source Site Code; see https://gdc.cancer.gov/resources-TCGA-users/TCGA-code-tables/tissue-source-site-codes for explanation of codes"),
  tumor_tissue_site STRING OPTIONS(description="The location on the body where the tumor exists; e.g. Brain, Ovary, Lung, etc."),
  tumor_type STRING OPTIONS(description="Tumor Type; e.g. Primary, Type 1, Type 2"),
  venous_invasion STRING OPTIONS(description="Indicator if large vessel or venous invasion was detected by surgery or presence in a tumor specimen; e.g. Yes, No"),
  vital_status STRING OPTIONS(description="Survival state of the participant; e.g. dead, alive"),
  weight INT64 OPTIONS(description="Weight of participant in kilograms"),
  year_of_diagnosis INT64 OPTIONS(description="Four digit year of the diagnosis"),
  year_of_tobacco_smoking_onset INT64 OPTIONS(description="Four-digit year that the participant started smoking; e.g. 2010")
)
OPTIONS(
  friendly_name="TCGA CLINICAL 2019 DEPRECATED",
  description="Data was extracted from the TCGA program in June 2019. This clinical information about patient cases also includes TCGA project information. More details: see https://docs.gdc.cancer.gov/Encyclopedia/pages/Clinical_Data/. This table has been deprecated. It has been copied to isb-cgc-bq.TCGA_versioned.clinical_gdc_2019_06. Please see isb-cgc-bq.TCGA.clinical_gdc_current for the most current table.",
  labels=[("data_type", "clinical_data"), ("category", "clinical_biospecimen_data"), ("access", "open"), ("status", "deprecated"), ("program", "tcga"), ("source", "gdc")]
);

CREATE TABLE `isb-cgc.TCGA_bioclin_v0.Biospecimen`
(
  sample_barcode STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA sample_barcode; e.g. TCGA-AB-2809-03A."),
  sample_gdc_id STRING OPTIONS(description="Unique GDC identifier for this sample (corresponds to the sample_barcode), eg a1ec9279-c1a6-4e58-97ed-9ec1f36187c5  --  this can be used to access more information from the GDC data portal"),
  case_barcode STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA patient/case barcode, eg TCGA-AB-2809 (the first 12 characters of the 16-character sample barcode)"),
  case_gdc_id STRING OPTIONS(description="GDC unique identifer for this case; e.g. 7b4ce492-ff40-4bf1-b3e8-75ff83e8746d. This identifier can be used to find more information at the GDC Data Portal ( https://portal.gdc.cancer.gov/cases/7b4ce492-ff40-4bf1-b3e8-75ff83e8746d )"),
  sample_type STRING OPTIONS(description="Two-digit sample_type code which forms part of the sample barcode e.g. 01,11,06, etc."),
  sample_type_name STRING OPTIONS(description="The longer name of the sample type; e.g. Primary Tumor, Recurrent Tumor, etc."),
  program_name STRING OPTIONS(description="Program Name, always TCGA (The Cancer Genome Atlas) in this table."),
  project_short_name STRING OPTIONS(description="Project name abbreviation; the program name appended with a project name abbreviation; e.g. TCGA-OV, etc."),
  batch_number INT64 OPTIONS(description="The BCR Batch Code; see https://gdc.cancer.gov/resources-TCGA-users/TCGA-code-tables/bcr-batch-codes for explanation of the codes"),
  bcr STRING OPTIONS(description="Biospecimen Core Resource; e.g. Nationwide Children's Hospital, Washington University"),
  days_to_collection FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="Time interval from the date of biospecimen collection to the date of initial pathologic diagnosis, represented as a calculated number of days."),
  days_to_sample_procurement FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The number of days from the date the patient was diagnosed to the date of the procedure that produced the sample."),
  is_ffpe STRING OPTIONS(description="Indicator to signify whether or not the tissue sample was fixed in formalin and embedded in paraffin (FFPE); almost always NO -- only a few (99) FFPE samples were included in the TCGA project"),
  num_portions INT64 OPTIONS(description="In some cases, a sample was divided into multiple portions -- up to 6 portions, but for most samples the number is 1 (or even 0)."),
  num_slides INT64 OPTIONS(description="In some cases, portions of a sample were placed onto multiple slides -- generally not more than 2, but occasionally more."),
  avg_percent_lymphocyte_infiltration FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The average percentage of infiltration by lymphocytes in a sample or specimen"),
  avg_percent_monocyte_infiltration FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The average percentage of infiltration by monocyte in a sample or specimen"),
  avg_percent_necrosis FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The average percentage of necrosis in a sample or specimen"),
  avg_percent_neutrophil_infiltration FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The average percentage of neutrophil infiltration in a sample or specimen"),
  avg_percent_normal_cells FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The average percentage of normal cells in a sample or specimen"),
  avg_percent_stromal_cells FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The average percentage of stromal cells in a sample or specimen"),
  avg_percent_tumor_cells FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The average percentage of tumor cells in a sample or specimen"),
  avg_percent_tumor_nuclei FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The average percentage of tumor nuclei in a sample or specimen"),
  max_percent_lymphocyte_infiltration FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The maximum percentage of infiltration by lymphocytes in a sample or specimen"),
  max_percent_monocyte_infiltration FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The maximum percentage of infiltration by monocytes in a sample or specimen"),
  max_percent_necrosis FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The maximum percentage of necrosis in a sample or specimen"),
  max_percent_neutrophil_infiltration FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The maximum percentage of neutrophil infiltration in a sample or specimen"),
  max_percent_normal_cells FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The maximum percentage of normal cells in a sample or specimen"),
  max_percent_stromal_cells FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The maximum percentage of stromal cells in a sample or specimen"),
  max_percent_tumor_cells FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The maximum percentage of tumor cells in a sample or specimen"),
  max_percent_tumor_nuclei FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The maximum percentage of tumor nuclei in a sample or specimen"),
  min_percent_lymphocyte_infiltration FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The minimum percentage of infiltration by lymphocytes in a sample or specimen"),
  min_percent_monocyte_infiltration FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The minimum percentage of infiltration by lymphocytes in a sample or specimen"),
  min_percent_necrosis FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The minimum percentage of necrosis in a sample or specimen"),
  min_percent_neutrophil_infiltration FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The minimum percentage of neutrophil infiltration in a sample or specimen"),
  min_percent_normal_cells FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The minimum percentage of normal cells in a sample or specimen"),
  min_percent_stromal_cells FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The minimum percentage of stromal cells in a sample or specimen"),
  min_percent_tumor_cells FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The minimum percentage of tumor cells in a sample or specimen"),
  min_percent_tumor_nuclei FLOAT64 OPTIONS(description="The minimum percentage of tumor nuclei in a sample or specimen")
)
OPTIONS(
  friendly_name="TCGA BIOSPECIMEN 2017 DEPRECATED",
  description="Data was extracted from the TCGA program in April 2017. It contains sample data for TCGA patient cases, originally based on the information provided by the TCGA biospecimen core resource (BCR) to the TCGA DCC in the form of xml files. Most patients (cases) provided two samples: one primary tumor sample and one blood normal sample, although other sample types exist, such as metastatic tumor samples, adjacent \"\"normal\"\" tissue samples, etc. There are, in a few cases, as many as 8 samples from a single case, although these may represent multiple \"vials\" from a smaller number of biospecimens. Also, some samples were obtained from cases for which no clinical information existed and which are therefore not represented in the Clinical table (which contains close to 200 fewer cases than this table does). More details: information about “clinical data elements” can be found at the NCI CDE (clinical data element) browser at https://cdebrowser.nci.nih.gov. This table has been deprecated. It has been copied to isb-cgc-bq.TCGA_versioned.biospecimen_gdc_2017_02. Please see isb-cgc-bq.TCGA.biospecimen_gdc_current for the most current table.",
  labels=[("data_type", "biospecimen"), ("category", "clinical_biospecimen_data"), ("access", "open"), ("status", "deprecated"), ("program", "tcga"), ("source", "gdc")]
);

CREATE TABLE `isb-cgc.TCGA_bioclin_v0.Annotations`
(
  project_short_name STRING OPTIONS(description="Project name abbreviation; the program name appended with a project name abbreviation; e.g. TCGA-OV, etc."),
  entity_barcode STRING OPTIONS(description="Barcode of the entity that this annotation applies to; often the same as the case barcode"),
  entity_type STRING OPTIONS(description="Type of the entity that this annotation applies to; e.g. Shipped Portion, Aliquot, Patient (which has the same meaning as Case), Analyte, etc."),
  category STRING OPTIONS(description="Annotation category; one of a relatively short list of phrases from a controlled-vocabulary; e.g. Item is noncanonical, Item flagged DNU, Prior malignancy, etc."),
  classification STRING OPTIONS(description="Annotation classification; e.g. Notification, CenterNotification, Observation, or Redaction"),
  notes STRING OPTIONS(description="Longer descriptive text about this annotation"),
  date_created STRING OPTIONS(description="Date on which this annotation was originally created; includes time-stamp and time-zone, eg 2011-03-14T18:00:42-04:00  --  dates range between March 2009 and June 2016"),
  date_edited STRING OPTIONS(description="Annotations were rarely edited, but if thery were (fewer than 10 out of over 6000 total annotations), this field indicates the date on which it was edited"),
  case_gdc_id STRING OPTIONS(description="GDC case identifier for the patient/case associated with this specific annotation"),
  case_barcode STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA patient/case barcode; e.g. TCGA-06-0119"),
  sample_barcode STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA sample barcode; e.g. TCGA-06-0119-01A (note that this field will be null if the annotation applies at a higher level than sample)"),
  aliquot_barcode STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA aliquot barcode; e.g. TCGA-06-0119-01A-08D-0216-06 (note that this field will be null if the annotation applies at a higher level than aliquot)")
)
OPTIONS(
  friendly_name="TCGA BIOCLINICAL ANNOTATIONS 2017 DEPRECATED",
  description="This data was generated from Annotations obtained from the TCGA DCC in June 2016. This annotation data for TCGA patient cases includes the GDC case identifier. It may have slight differences from the annotations available at the GDC. This table has been deprecated. It has been copied to isb-cgc-bq.TCGA_versioned.annotations_gdc_2017_04. Please see isb-cgc-bq.TCGA.annotations_gdc_current for the most current table.",
  labels=[("data_type", "clinical_supplement"), ("category", "clinical_biospecimen_data"), ("access", "open"), ("status", "deprecated"), ("program", "tcga"), ("source", "gdc")]
);

CREATE TABLE `isb-cgc.TCGA_bioclin_v0.clinical_v1_1`
(
  case_gdc_id STRING,
  case_barcode STRING,
  program_name STRING,
  disease_code STRING,
  project_short_name STRING,
  age_at_diagnosis INT64,
  age_began_smoking_in_years STRING,
  anatomic_neoplasm_subdivision STRING,
  batch_number INT64,
  bcr STRING,
  bmi FLOAT64,
  clinical_M STRING,
  clinical_N STRING,
  clinical_stage STRING,
  clinical_T STRING,
  colorectal_cancer STRING,
  country STRING,
  days_to_birth INT64,
  days_to_death INT64,
  days_to_initial_pathologic_diagnosis INT64,
  days_to_last_followup INT64,
  days_to_last_known_alive INT64,
  days_to_submitted_specimen_dx STRING,
  ethnicity STRING,
  gender STRING,
  gleason_score_combined STRING,
  h_pylori_infection STRING,
  height INT64,
  histological_type STRING,
  history_of_colon_polyps STRING,
  history_of_neoadjuvant_treatment STRING,
  hpv_calls STRING,
  hpv_status STRING,
  icd_10 STRING,
  icd_o_3_histology STRING,
  icd_o_3_site STRING,
  lymphatic_invasion STRING,
  lymphnodes_examined STRING,
  lymphovascular_invasion_present STRING,
  menopause_status STRING,
  mononucleotide_and_dinucleotide_marker_panel_analysis_status STRING,
  neoplasm_histologic_grade STRING,
  new_tumor_event_after_initial_treatment BOOL,
  number_of_lymphnodes_examined INT64,
  number_of_lymphnodes_positive_by_he STRING,
  number_pack_years_smoked INT64,
  other_dx STRING,
  other_malignancy_anatomic_site STRING,
  other_malignancy_histological_type STRING,
  other_malignancy_type STRING,
  pathologic_M STRING,
  pathologic_N STRING,
  pathologic_stage STRING,
  pathologic_T STRING,
  person_neoplasm_cancer_status STRING,
  pregnancies STRING,
  primary_neoplasm_melanoma_dx STRING,
  primary_therapy_outcome_success STRING,
  psa_value STRING,
  race STRING,
  residual_tumor STRING,
  stopped_smoking_year INT64,
  tobacco_smoking_history INT64,
  tss_code STRING,
  tumor_tissue_site STRING,
  tumor_type STRING,
  venous_invasion STRING,
  vital_status STRING,
  weight INT64,
  year_of_diagnosis INT64,
  year_of_tobacco_smoking_onset INT64,
  project_name STRING
)
OPTIONS(
  description="Copy of clinical_v1 with project_name from Clinical appended to it."
);

CREATE TABLE `isb-cgc.TCGA_bioclin_v0.Clinical`
(
  program_name STRING OPTIONS(description="Program Name, always TCGA (The Cancer Genome Atlas) in this table."),
  case_barcode STRING OPTIONS(description="TCGA patient/case barcode; e.g. TCGA-06-0119"),
  case_gdc_id STRING OPTIONS(description="GDC unique identifer for this case; e.g. 7b4ce492-ff40-4bf1-b3e8-75ff83e8746d. This identifier can be used to find more information at the GDC Data Portal ( https://portal.gdc.cancer.gov/cases/7b4ce492-ff40-4bf1-b3e8-75ff83e8746d )"),
  program_dbgap_accession_number STRING OPTIONS(description="Program dbGaP accession number, eg phs000178"),
  project_short_name STRING OPTIONS(description="Project name abbreviation; the program name appended with a project name abbreviation; e.g. TCGA-OV, etc."),
  project_name STRING OPTIONS(description="Project Name; frequently the same as or similar to the project disease type eg   Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia - Phase II   or   Breast Invasive Carcinoma   etc"),
  disease_code STRING OPTIONS(description="A code representing the type of cancer. Values can be found at https://gdc.cancer.gov/resources-TCGA-users/TCGA-code-tables/TCGA-study-abbreviations; e.g. OV, GBM, LUAD"),
  gender STRING OPTIONS(description="Participant gender; e.g. Male, Female"),
  vital_status STRING OPTIONS(description="Survival state of the participant; e.g. dead, alive"),
  race STRING OPTIONS(description="The race of a participant, independent from ethnicity; e.g. White, Black or African American, Asian, Native Hawaiian or other Pacific Islander, American Indian or Alaska Native"),
  ethnicity STRING OPTIONS(description="The ethnic origination of a participant, independent from race; e.g. Not Hispanic or Latino, Hispanic or Latino"),
  age_at_diagnosis INT64 OPTIONS(description="Age, in years, at which a condition or disease was first diagnosed"),
  days_to_birth INT64 OPTIONS(description="Days since birth (a negative value, relative to the date of diagnosis which is considered to be t=0)"),
  days_to_death INT64 OPTIONS(description="If vital_status indicates 'dead', then this is the number of days to death (a positive value) relative to the date of diagnosis."),
  days_to_initial_pathologic_diagnosis INT64 OPTIONS(description="The number of days to initial pathologic diagnosis"),
  days_to_last_followup INT64 OPTIONS(description="If vital_status indicates 'alive', then this is the number of days from the date of diagnosis to the last followup (communication contact)."),
  days_to_last_known_alive INT64 OPTIONS(description="Number of days from the date of diagnosis to the last day on which a person was known to be alive. This field is a combination of the days_to_last_followup and days_to death fields. Therefore, this field can be used whether the vital_status is 'alive' or 'dead'."),
  days_to_submitted_specimen_dx INT64 OPTIONS(description="Numeric value to represent the day of the diagnosis for the submitted sample."),
  clinical_stage STRING OPTIONS(description="The stage of the cancer, based on results of tests done before surgery, such as physical exams and imaging scans; e.g. Stage I, Stage II, Stage III, Stage IV"),
  clinical_T STRING OPTIONS(description="The clinical T score is a rating of the extent of the primary tumor, based on results of tests done before surgery, such as physical exams and imaging scans; e.g. T1, T2, T3, T4"),
  clinical_N STRING OPTIONS(description="The clinical N score is a rating of the extent of cancer within nearby lymph nodes, based on results of tests done before surgery, such as physical exams and imaging scans; e.g. N1, N2, N3"),
  clinical_M STRING OPTIONS(description="The clinical M score is a rating of metastasis, that is, how much cancer has spread to distant sites. It is based on results of tests done before surgery, such as physical exams and imaging scans; e.g. MX, M0, M1"),
  pathologic_stage STRING OPTIONS(description="The stage of the cancer, based on surgery or biopsy; e.g. Stage I, Stage II, Stage III, Stage IV"),
